urvivors looked for hope in what seemed, at times, like a hopeless situation.Drawn in a restrained, inviting style, Taking Turns is an open, honest look at suffering, grief, and resilience among a community of medical professionals and patients at the heart of the AIDS epidemic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAIDS (Disease)xNursingvComic books, strips, etc. 0aHIV infectionsxNursingvComic books, strips, etc. 0aMedicinevComic books, strips, etc. 7aCOMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS / Nonfiction / Biography & Memoir.2bisacsh1 aCzerwiec, MK, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishz978311075417908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021z9783110753943oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074510840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781637790182?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781637790182423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781637790182/original  a978-3-11-074510-8  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075417-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-PLWb2021